\begin_layout Standard
In this paper,
 we test a decentralized alternative:
 we aggregate the experiences of farmers themselves into a signal of seed performance.
 Building on a well-established literature documenting the importance of peers in agricultural technology adoption 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "foster1995learning,https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0297.2006.01115.x,10.1257/aer.100.1.35"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 we test whether aggregating peers’ experiences into a public signal of seed performance can improve market outcomes through three channels:
 belief updating about agro-dealer seed relative to outside options,
 dealer sorting conditional on purchasing from agro-dealers,
 or supply-side improvements in seed preservation.
